  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dad\u0dca \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0daf\u0dba\u0dda \u0d86\u0dba\u0dd4 \u0d85\u0db4\u0dda\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dad \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Life expectancy in the US is falling",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The average American's life expectancy has dropped significantly between 2019 and 2021, according to a report published by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).",
        "It is also considered the first two-year decline since 1961-1963.",
        "In the past two years, life expectancy in the United States has decreased by 2.7 years, and the average life expectancy has fallen to 76.1 years, returning to 1996 levels.",
        "According to the CDC, the primary factor in reducing life expectancy is the Covid-19 pandemic. It has contributed to the deaths of over a million Americans.",
        "Before the pandemic, heart disease had long been the top reported cause of death in the United States."
      ],
